==English==
===Noun===
'''supply chain'''
# Aligns the capabilities of suppliers, manufacturers, channel partners & customers in order to control the physical flow of products from source to point of use.

•	Integrates the activities of all members of the chain to produce higher levels of performance than can be achieved individually.

•	The focus is on aligning practices used by different businesses that together produce the product & service the customer … to yield superior business performance for all involved.

•	Provides customers with improved service and decreased cost by blending activities of all participants to increase productivity and reduce costs for all involved.

•	Replaces adversarial relationships with one that benefits from mutual dependency and more profitable growth for all.

•	For example:
	– Elimination of duplication
– Just In Time manufacturing
– Continuous replenishment
– Quick Response
.
